        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 3:15PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 315 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles southeast of Salisbury, or near Rockwell, moving northeast at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rockwell, Mt Pleasant, Faith, High Rock Lake, Granite Quarry, and
Gold Hill.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
